Cosatu's General Secretary, Bheki Ntshalintshali speaks to #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Cosatu says the latest interest rate hike will bleed workers and suffocate the economy further. The federation says the 75 basis points hike was not done in the interest of the people, but those of the lenders. It's calling on the government to intervene and look at external factors influencing inflation. Watch the video above for more details.